Description: Wasta packaging of WINE (64bit) for application stability
 A stable version of WINE is preferred so that any user-level wine updates will
 not interfere with application stability.
 .
 The wine version here was obtained by using PlayOnLinux, then is placed in
 /opt/wasta-wine64. Since this folder is not part of $PATH any use of
 wasta-wine64 would need to explicitly call these /opt/wasta-wine64 executables.
 .
 Launchpad attempts to re-build binaries and it has trouble adding the :i386
 version of packages needed as 'Build-Depends' so instead a .tar.gz is made of
 the PlayOnLinux wine folder, performing a transform from the wine version to
 'wasta-wine64' for consistency. Here is the command used to create the .tar.gz
 for wine version 6.7-staging, for example:
 tar -zcvf wasta-wine64.tar.gz 6.7-staging --transform='s@^6.7-staging@wasta-wine64@g'
 .
 An md5sum is then made of this tar.gz:
 md5sum wasta-wine64.tar.gz > wasta-wine64.tar.gz.md5
 .
 Then, this will need to be split into 45MB chunks to comply with github
 size limits: split -d -b 45M wasta-wine64.tar.gz wasta-wine64-
 .
 The postinst will then re-assemble the chunks and check the md5sum:
 cat wasta-wine64-* > wasta-wine64.tar.gz
 and then extract to /opt/wasta-wine64/
 .
 The prerm will remove the /opt/wasta-wine64 directory to clean up.
 .
 To set the Dependencies and Recommends for wine, reference those listed at
 https://dl.winehq.org/wine-builds/ubuntu/dists/focal/main/binary-amd64/Packages
 for the wine-staging-amd64 for the desired wine version and also
 https://dl.winehq.org/wine-builds/ubuntu/dists/focal/main/binary-i386/Packages
 for the wine-staging-i386 for the desired wine version (manually add ':i386'to
 the dependencies of wine-staging to provide 32bit build capability).
